headlines.description: — Kyle Kuzma hit a go-ahead 3-pointer with 12 seconds left as the Washington Wizards scored the final five points in a 97-94 victory over the Cleveland Cavaliers on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wizards beat Cavaliers 97-94 on Kuzma's late 3-pointer

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant scored 30 points and James Harden had his 59th career triple double in the Brooklyn Nets' 123-90 victory over the Orlando Magic on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kevin Durant, James Harden lead Nets past Magic, 123-90

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum had 22 points, 12 rebounds and seven assists in the Boston Celtics' 104-88 victory over the Toronto Raptors on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jayson Tatum helps Celtics beat Raptors, 104-88

events.name: Milwaukee Bucks at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Pat Connaughton kept another lost lead from becoming another lost game against the New York Knicks.
headlines.shortLinkText: Connaughton helps Bucks recover, top Knicks after blown lead

headlines.description: — Jerami Grant scored a season-high 35 points to help the Detroit Pistons beat the Houston Rockets 112-104 on Wednesday night in a matchup of two of the worst teams in the NBA.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grant has season-high 35 points, Pistons top Rockets 112-104

headlines.description: — There is no secret to Lonzo Ball's improved 3-point shooting. He put the work in, and it's paying off.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ball, LaVine lead Bulls past Mavericks 117-107

headlines.description: — Kelly Oubre Jr. scored a season-best 37 points on 13-of-17 shooting and the Charlotte Hornets beat the Memphis Grizzlies 118-108 on Wednesday night to snap a five-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Oubre scores 37 points, helps Hornets beat Grizzlies 118-108

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Lu Dort capped off one of his better shooting nights of the young season with three clutch free throws and a dunk to punctuate Oklahoma City's third straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dort's 27 points lead Thunder past reeling Pelicans, 108-100

events.name: Sacramento Kings at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Spurs coach Gregg Popovich realizes this season is going to be one of growth and development for his young roster. Consider this blowout victory over the Sacramento Kings evidence of a lesson learned.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray scores 26, Spurs hit 18 3s to blitz Kings 136-117

headlines.description: — Will Barton scored a season-high 30 points, helping to make up for the absence of suspended star Nikola Jokic as the Denver Nuggets hung on to beat the Indiana Pacers 101-98 Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barton scores 30, Nuggets beat Pacers 101-98 without Jokic

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Phoenix Suns forward Frank Kaminsky bested his career high in points with a very Kaminsky-esque move, faking out Portland's Norman Powell with a smooth up and under that he finished with a finger roll at the rim.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kaminsky has career night, scores 31 points in Suns' victory

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Andrew Wiggins drove the baseline for an emphatic one-handed slam right over old teammate Karl-Anthony Towns, and it sure felt sweet.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wiggins dominates former Wolves mates with season-best 35

events.name: Miami Heat at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — With the most important player on both of these super-teams out of action, the Heat's visit to the Lakers had to be decided by which supporting cast came through down the stretch.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lakers rally late in regulation, hold off Heat 120-117 in OT
